The source code is contained in the evm.c file

The compilation command for the file is

make all

To execute the command you need to use different command line arguments. A command line argument has to be given by default or it will not work.

./evm -k starting address(eg: 101) count(eg :16)

this is to load and print the code in memory

./evm -k starting address(eg: 101) count(eg :16) Number1(3) Number2(4)

This will load the program in the memory and print the output using the numbers you provided.

./evm -x Number1 Number2 this load the program in memory and store number 1 and number 2 in memory and print out the sequence so that it can be given output to the machine

./evm -i is used to take the input from the user

